Lawrence L. WELLER, Appellant, v. HORSE HEAVEN IRRIGATION DISTRICT, etc., et al., Appellees. No. 7067. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. Oct 16, 1933. W. F. Crowe, of Walla Walla, Wash., for appellant. Harold H. Hartman, of Seattle, Wash., Fred J. Cunningham, of Spokane, Wash., and Warren H. Lewis, of Seattle, Wash., for appellees Hartman and others. F. B. Sharpstein, of Walla Walla, Wash., for appellees Horse Heaven Irrigation District and Directors.

Before WILBUR, SAWTELLE, and GARRECHT, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Upon stipulation of counsel for all parties, ordered appeal dismissed; mandate forthwith.
